fulfillWithdrawal(bytes32,address,addres.details: The Airnode sends the funds to the sponsor through this method to emit an event that indicates that the withdrawal request has been fulfilled

requestWithdrawal(address,address).details: We do not need to use the withdrawal request parameters in the request ID hash to validate them at the node-side because all of the parameters are used during fulfillment and will get validated on-chain. The first withdrawal request a sponsor will make will cost slightly higher gas than the rest due to how the request counter is implemented.

params.sponsorWallet: Sponsor wallet that the withdrawal is requested from

sponsorToWithdrawalRequestCount.details: Can be used to calculate the ID of the next withdrawal request the sponsor will make

withdrawalRequestIdToParameters.details: Hash of expected fulfillment parameters are kept to verify that the fulfillment will be done with the correct parameters

devdoc.title: Contract that implements logic for withdrawals from sponsor wallets
